President Trump spoke at a gathering of the International Union of Operating Engineers in Crosby, Texas, where he praised the workers for their contribution to the American energy industry. He highlighted the United States' position as the top producer of oil and natural gas in the world and the growth in jobs and production that has occurred under his administration. The President also signed two executive orders aimed at expediting the approval process for energy infrastructure projects and modernizing regulations for LNG export terminals. He emphasized the importance of training and job opportunities for American workers and praised the union for committing to train almost 550,000 individuals for future jobs.